    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so im having a bit of a hard time w my dev team. we keep getting these random feature requests from stakeholders right in the middle of our sprints and it's totally messing up our velocity. what are some actual ways to manage scope creep so this stops happening? thanks",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To manage scope creep, consider setting clear boundaries with stakeholders by establishing a first review process before accepting any new requirements. This can involve a brief discussion to determine if the request aligns with the existing project goals. You can also create a 'green light' process where requests need to meet specific criteria, such as business value or alignment with existing features. Additionally, consider using agile scaling frameworks like LeSS or SAFe, which provide structured processes for handling scope fluctuations.",
      "source": "target",
